git config --global user.name "your_username"
git config --global user.email "your_email"

git init                       // Initialize empty git repository
git status                     // Check status of files in git repo

git add --a                    // Add all files to staging area

git commit -m "commit_message"       // To commit changes (capture snapshot)
git log                              // View all commits history


// To create new repository on command line

echo "# Repository-Name" >> README.md
git init
git add README.md
git commit -m "first commit"
git branch -M main
git remote add origin https://github.com/satwikverma/Strivers-A2Z-DSA.git
git push -u origin main


// To push existing repository from command line

git remote add origin https://github.com/satwikverma/Strivers-A2Z-DSA.git                // creating a remote
git branch -M main
git push -u origin main                                                                  // pushing to the remote repository

Note :
Before pushing the changes to remote repository, we need access / permission to do so and we can do that by using SSH keys.

Step-1 : Create new SSH key

-> Search "ssh keys github on google"
-> Open first link
-> Follow steps to add

Step-2 : Add the SSH key to your account

-> Open link in above link's point number 3 .
-> Follow steps to add that SSH key to your github account
